[Acts 7:54](../../../bib/kjv/act007.htm#054.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_054">act 7:54</span></span>

When they heard

They had brought false witnesses against Stephen; he bears true witness
against them, quoting the testimony of writers they owned to be
inspired. He speaks of the persistent rejection of God and His servants
by the nation til at last it is brought home to themselves, and arouses
the maddened enmity of their hearts. It was the final trial of the
nation.

